  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "UI/UX Designer",
  "description": "<p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li>Design intuitive, user-friendly interfaces for employers and contractors.</li></ul><ul><li>Conduct user research, interviews, and usability testing to inform design decisions.</li></ul><ul><li>Create wireframes, prototypes, and high-fidelity mockups for product features.</li></ul><ul><li>Collaborate closely with product managers and engineers to ensure seamless implementation.</li></ul><ul><li>Maintain design consistency across platforms and ensure accessibility standards are met.</li></ul><p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li>Proven experience in UI/UX design with a strong portfolio of web and mobile applications.</li></ul><ul><li>Proficiency in design tools (Figma, Sketch, Adobe XD).</li></ul><ul><li>Strong understanding of user-centered design principles and interaction design.</li></ul><ul><li>Experience conducting user research and usability testing.</li></ul><ul><li>Ability to balance aesthetics with functionality and business requirements.</li></ul>",
